md:
giải nghĩa từ "migrate" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan và các từ trái nghĩa.

* Migrate (verb) - Di cư, di chuyển
	+ Meaning: To move from one place to another, especially in search of better living conditions or opportunities.
	+ Example: Many people migrate to cities in search of better job opportunities.
	+ Related words: immigration, emigration, relocation
	+ Antonyms: settle, stay

* Migrate (verb) - Di chuyển (dữ liệu, ứng dụng)
	+ Meaning: To transfer or move data or an application from one system or platform to another.
	+ Example: The company needs to migrate its data to a new server.
	+ Related words: transfer, move, upgrade
	+ Antonyms: stay, remain

* Migration (noun) - Di cư, di chuyển
	+ Meaning: The process of moving from one place to another, especially in search of better living conditions or opportunities.
	+ Example: The migration of people from rural areas to cities has led to urbanization.
	+ Related words: immigration, emigration, relocation
	+ Antonyms: settlement, stability

* Migration (noun) - Di chuyển (dữ liệu, ứng dụng)
	+ Meaning: The process of transferring or moving data or an application from one system or platform to another.
	+ Example: The migration of the company's database to a new system took several weeks.
	+ Related words: transfer, move, upgrade
	+ Antonyms: stay, remain
